Pre-Game Insights: Eastern Conference foes Cleveland and Milwaukee face off.
Cleveland Cavaliers are currently first in the Eastern Conference with a 7-0 record.
Milwaukee Bucks are currently 14th in the Eastern Conference with a 1-5 record.
Cleveland finished 48-34 overall, 11-5 in Central Division play and 26-15 at home last season.
The Cavaliers averaged 16.6 points off of turnovers, 13.6 second-chance points and 34.4 bench points last season.
Milwaukee finished 49-33 overall and 34-18 in Eastern Conference games during the 2023-24 season.
The Bucks averaged 119.0 points per game last season, 47.1 in the paint, 14.5 off of turnovers and 12.7 on fast breaks.
Injuries for the Cavaliers include Caris LeVert (day to day, knee), Emoni Bates (out, knee), and Max Strus (out, ankle).
Injuries for the Bucks include Khris Middleton (out, ankle).
